President Obama has signed a disaster declaration for the state of Montana following a tornado that occurred on June 11, 2016. The declaration allows for federal aid to supplement state and local recovery efforts in the affected area. Funding will be available for emergency work, repair or replacement of damaged facilities, and hazard mitigation measures. Nancy M. Casper has been appointed as the Federal Coordinating Officer for federal recovery operations in the affected area. Further designations may be made if requested by the state and deemed necessary based on damage assessments. For more information, contact the FEMA News Desk.